title: ONHA - KODAK (2024)
description: The music video for "Kodak" by ONHA, directed by Nitram, showcases the artist moving through different lively and surreal environments that correspond to playlists on a girl's phone. In one standout scene, ONHA is turned into a basketball, remaining the focal point during a game. The video is praised for its ambitious concept and impressive visual effects, making it a visually captivating experience.

title: Pharrell Williams - Cash In Cash Out (2022)
description: "Cash In Cash Out" is a song produced by American musician Pharrell Williams, featuring vocals from Atlanta-based rapper 21 Savage and American rapper Tyler, the Creator. Written by all three, it was released as a single through Columbia Records on June 10, 2022. Williams first teased the song on his TikTok account June 6, 2022. An accompanying music video was released, featuring a zoetrope-inspired CG animation style.

title: 21 Savage - redrum (2024)
description: The music video for "Redrum" by 21 Savage, featured on his album "American Dream," is directed by Danny Seth and showcases a return to the artist's roots in London. It contrasts iconic landmarks with the grittier areas of Brixton, symbolizing the song's themes. The track itself, produced by London on da Track, samples "Serenata do Adeus" and incorporates elements from "The Shining," including the famous line "Here's Johnny!" Despite some opinions that the video could have more directly referenced "The Shining's" iconic scenes, it has been well-received for its artistic representation and Savage's performance.

title: Aminé - Charmander (2021)
description: In the 2021 music video "Charmander" by Aminé, the artist retreats to a secluded cabin in the woods, symbolizing a quest for peace and introspection away from the pressures of fame. The video is characterized by a warm, earthy color palette and natural light, capturing the tranquil beauty of the forest setting. The nostalgic reference to Pokémon through the title "Charmander" adds a whimsical contrast to the mature themes of self-discovery and isolation.

title: AJ Tracey - Bubble Bath (2024)
description: The music video for "Bubble Bath" by AJ Tracey, released in 2024, is set in a lively West London nail shop, directed by LateMilk. The video features vibrant, energetic scenes that reflect the song's upbeat and catchy vibe. It highlights the fusion of contemporary urban culture with playful, colorful visuals, showcasing AJ Tracey in various stylish setups, interacting with people in the nail shop, and performing the song with charisma and flair. The setting and visuals create a fun, engaging atmosphere that complements the track's infectious rhythm and lyrics.
